english_definitions: to find (e.g. an error in a book)

to watch a batted ball go into the stands
to shelve (a plan, deliberation on a bill, etc.)
to have someone related or close to you die
to take care of somebody until he dies
to get a better opinion of
to see in a more positive light
how to look at something (e.g. noh, train schedule)
to take an extensive view of
to turn a blind eye to
to let (a good ball) go by
calling on someone who is ill
